# ACL Tables (Inter‑VLAN + Port‑Level)

These tables define the exact allowed and denied flows per VLAN, including source, destination, ports, and purpose.  
They are used to generate the final Cisco ACL configuration.

---

# VLAN 10 — Identity (ACL‑IN‑VLAN10)

| Source VLAN | Destination | Ports Allowed | Purpose | Action |
|-------------|-------------|---------------|---------|--------|
| 30 (VM) | 10 | 53, 88, 135, 389, 445, 636, 3268, 3269, 123 | AD/DNS | Allow |
| 99 (PAWs) | 10 | All AD/DNS ports + 3389, 5985, 5986, 443 | Admin | Allow |
| 20 (ESXi) | 10 | 53, 88, 389, 445 (optional) | ESXi AD integration | Allow (conditional) |
| 20 (ESXi) | 10 | All others | Protect Identity | Deny |
| 90 (Router Inside) | 10 | All | Protect Identity | Deny |
| 100 (OOB) | 10 | All | Protect Identity | Deny |

